<title>UK: Daimler - return on capital employed to rise.</title>
<headline>Daimler - return on capital employed to rise.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Daimler-Benz AG said on Thursday its return on capital employed would improve in 1997 to at least eight to nine percent, up from 5.2 percent at the end of 1996.</p>
<p>&quot;If we assume second half proift would be the same as the first half, then our full-year return on capital employed would be eight to nine percent,&quot; Daimler chief Juergen Schrempp told reporters at the company's half-year results conference.</p>
<p>-- Bonn Newsroom, +49-228 26097150</p>
